This paper deals with representing and reasoning with annotated Semantic Web data, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as deductive reasoning and querying. It also involves database (DB) management and querying, as well as machine learning (LG) for handling fuzzy annotations. The paper also addresses the development of a query language, which falls under programming languages (PL) and software engineering (SE).
